This paper focuses on the development of automatic de-identification systems for medical data, specifically longitudinal clinical narratives. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of conditional random fields (CRF) and deep learning, which are also covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper addresses the legal and ethical issues surrounding the use of medical data, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
